ðŸ“˜ SQL COMPLETE PRACTICE NOTES
(3-Table JOINs + DQL + DML + DDL)
ðŸ”¹ IMPORTANT CONCEPTS (INTERVIEW READY)
1ï¸âƒ£ DQL â€“ Data Query Language

Used to fetch data

SELECT

2ï¸âƒ£ DML â€“ Data Manipulation Language

Used to modify data

INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE

3ï¸âƒ£ DDL â€“ Data Definition Language

Used to modify table structure

CREATE, ALTER, DROP

4ï¸âƒ£ JOIN (MOST IMPORTANT FOR PDF)

Used to combine multiple tables using relationships

JOIN	Meaning
INNER JOIN	Matching records only
LEFT JOIN	All left table + matching right
LEFT JOIN + IS NULL	Find â€œno matchâ€ records
5ï¸âƒ£ GROUP BY & HAVING

GROUP BY â†’ groups rows

HAVING â†’ filters groups (after aggregation)

6ï¸âƒ£ Aggregates
COUNT(), SUM(), AVG()

7ï¸âƒ£ PDF-LEVEL GOLD RULES â­

One-to-many join â†’ COUNT can lie

Use COUNT(DISTINCT ...) if needed

Select only columns asked

Dates must be in quotes

LEFT JOIN + IS NULL â†’ â€œno recordsâ€

ðŸ§± SCHEMA USED (CUSTOMERSâ€“ORDERSâ€“ORDER_ITEMS)
1ï¸âƒ£ customers (DDL)
CREATE TABLE customers (
    customer_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    customer_name VARCHAR(50),
    city VARCHAR(50)
);

2ï¸âƒ£ orders (DDL)
CREATE TABLE orders (
    order_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    customer_id INT,
    order_date DATE,
    FOREIGN KEY (customer_id) REFERENCES customers(customer_id)
);

3ï¸âƒ£ order_items (DDL)
CREATE TABLE order_items (
    item_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    order_id INT,
    product_name VARCHAR(50),
    quantity INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (order_id) REFERENCES orders(order_id)
);

