ðŸŽ¯ QUESTION 1 â€” EASY
Display customer name, city, order date, product name
âœ… SQL
SELECT 
    c.customer_name,
    c.city,
    o.order_date,
    i.product_name
FROM customers c
JOIN orders o ON c.customer_id = o.customer_id
JOIN order_items i ON o.order_id = i.order_id;

ðŸ“Š OUTPUT
name	city	date	product
Rahul	Hyderabad	2024-01-10	Laptop
Rahul	Hyderabad	2024-01-10	Mouse
Anita	Bangalore	2024-01-12	Keyboard
Rahul	Hyderabad	2024-01-15	Monitor
ðŸ§  Explanation

3-table INNER JOIN

One row per product

ðŸŽ¯ QUESTION 2 â€” MEDIUM
Orders placed in January 2024
âœ… SQL
SELECT 
    c.customer_name,
    c.city,
    o.order_date
FROM customers c
JOIN orders o ON c.customer_id = o.customer_id
WHERE o.order_date BETWEEN '2024-01-01' AND '2024-01-31';

ðŸ“Š OUTPUT
name	city	date
Rahul	Hyderabad	2024-01-10
Anita	Bangalore	2024-01-12
Rahul	Hyderabad	2024-01-15
ðŸ§  Explanation

Dates must be in quotes

BETWEEN is clean & readable

ðŸŽ¯ QUESTION 3 â€” MEDIUM
Total quantity ordered by each customer
âœ… SQL
SELECT 
    c.customer_name,
    SUM(i.quantity) AS total_products
FROM customers c
JOIN orders o ON c.customer_id = o.customer_id
JOIN order_items i ON o.order_id = i.order_id
GROUP BY c.customer_id, c.customer_name;

ðŸ“Š OUTPUT
customer	total_products
Rahul	4
Anita	1
ðŸ§  Explanation

GROUP BY customer

SUM quantities across orders

ðŸŽ¯ QUESTION 4 â€” HARD
Customers who placed more than 1 order
âœ… SQL
SELECT 
    c.customer_name,
    COUNT(o.order_id) AS number_of_orders
FROM customers c
JOIN orders o ON c.customer_id = o.customer_id
GROUP BY c.customer_id, c.customer_name
HAVING COUNT(o.order_id) > 1;

ðŸ“Š OUTPUT
customer	orders
Rahul	2
ðŸ§  Explanation

No need to join order_items

HAVING filters aggregated results

ðŸŽ¯ QUESTION 5 â€” HARDEST
Customers who did NOT place any order
âœ… SQL
SELECT 
    c.customer_name,
    c.city
FROM customers c
LEFT JOIN orders o ON c.customer_id = o.customer_id
WHERE o.order_id IS NULL;

ðŸ“Š OUTPUT
customer	city
Suresh	Chennai
ðŸ§  Explanation

LEFT JOIN keeps all customers

NULL order_id â†’ no orders
